We have 27 steps in our largest workflow and if everyone where to get emails on each and every step of the way the notification is worthless.  For instance, when the ticket is in its open stage, we don't want any emails to go out.  This is when the reporter may be make 6 ,7 9 changes to the ticket to get it just right.  I don't need to get that info when I am creating the ticket and configuring it.  When the ticket is in Feature / Requirements, we want our account executives and all to be involved in the discussion, but once it gets to the LOE, Technical Design, programming, etc.  They don't want to be spammed with all these emails.

Having a "Don't Mail Yourself" option would be nice too.

This feature is most important on the Issue Update, Issue Assigned, Issue Comment.  The other are important too, but these are the culprits that create the spamming effect.

When commenting an issue the comment's header looks like this: 
{panel}*Conan Commenter - 24/Dec/09 09:48 PM* \\ OK{panel}

If the issue is within a project that has a lot of transitions in its workflow it would be nice to know if comment was given when doing a transition.

Thus, new comment header should look something like this:
{panel}*Conan Commenter - 24/Dec/09 09:48 PM Waiting approval -> Approved* \\ OK {panel}

Now it would be easier to see with one glance who has done which transition and with what comment. This information is quite hard to get if there are many comments and many transitions (there is [Transitions Panel|http://code.google.com/p/jira-suite-utilities/wiki/DetailedDescription] which helps a little with this problem). I believe that my proposition would be simple to implement and really usable for many JIRA-installations.

